Vice President Mike Pence visited York, Pennsylvania to discuss tax cuts and reform with local business owners. Pence emphasized the importance of tax relief for working families, small businesses, and family farms. He also highlighted the need to simplify the tax code and lower taxes on businesses to increase competitiveness. Pence listened to the concerns and perspectives of the business owners in attendance and promised to carry their feedback back to Congress. He urged the American people to reach out to their elected representatives and advocate for tax cuts.